MenuSectionDialog.section-description: Your career branding is the first touch point between your brand and the page visitors. Begin customizing your page by uploading your own logo and favicon, and updating the menu section.This section of your page includes the buttons that redirect candidates to internal pages within your site, or to other pages. To get started, simply add the title, link type and link for each designated button.
MenuSectionDialog.title: Title

HeaderSectionDialog.section-description: Your career page drives top talent to apply, builds your employer brand and becomes a resource for candidates to learn more about you, and what it would be like to work at your company. This section will appear at the top of your page. Start by writing a catchy headline and description to attract top talent. Then, set up your background color and image, to bring your career page to life.
HeaderSectionDialog.title: Title

MediaAndTextSectionDialog.section-description: This section is used to creatively highlight anything on your career page by including a supporting image or video. Simply upload an image or video to be shown alongside customized text. These can be used for team testimonials or the About Us section. You can also adjust the media and format the text to your own preferences.

OpeningsSectionDialog.section-description: In this section, you can showcase all your recent job openings to potential candidates. We like to keep things simpleâ€¦ so just add a title and a thorough description, to excite top candidates to apply.

GridsSectionDialog.section-description:
The most successful career pages have grids that showcase their perks and benefits, what the company offers, and more. These grids are some of the first things that candidates look for and can play a huge role in whether or not they apply.

In this section, you can add as many grids as you want. All you have to do is customize the titles and descriptions, and upload the images of your choice. We've also designed optional icons that you may use, so you can choose a style that best aligns with your website's branding.

GallerySectionDialog.section-description: A gallery in your career page is best used for showing off company photos. Whether it's the office space, group employee photos, or your products. They give your candidates a behind-the-scenes look at​ what it would be like to work with your company. You can also include a catchy header and description!
GallerySectionDialog.title: Title

TeamMembersSectionDialog.section-description: In this section, introduce your awesome team to prospective candidates. Upload their images, add a description for each, and choose to link their social media accounts if you like.

SliderSectionDialog.section-description: Make the best out of your client testimonials and add them to your career page. Or, simply add the logos of your renowned clients. Through powerful testimonials, you can prompt candidates to apply to your job vacancies faster. In this section, add the title, testimonial, and image for each person.
SliderSectionDialog.title: Title

LocationSectionDialog.section-description: Add your office location(s) to your career page through this section. It's best to include a specific address so that candidates know exactly where you're located!

QuotesSectionDialog.section-description: Add quotes or testimonials from employees, to add extra credibility to your career page. These testimonials will show candidates what makes your company an attractive place to work. In this section, add your employeesâ€™ pictures and quotes. Try to include perspectives from a variety of employees across different departments!

PartnersSectionDialog.section-description: Rely on your trusted partners to add extra credibility and value to your career page. Add a catchy headline, description, and the logo for each designated partner.

SuccessStoriesSectionDialog.section-description: Adding success stories to your career page adds visibility, clarity, and credibility around the value and application of your products or services. It shows candidates the positive impact your company has had on clients. In this section, add the success stories along with their designated title, description, and related image.

JobCategoriesSectionDialog.section-description: Adding job categories enhances the job searching process on your career page. It also makes it easier for candidates to surf through your job vacancies. Simply edit the job categoryâ€™s title, add the description, select the category, and upload a relevant image.
JobCategoriesSectionDialog.title: Title

FooterSectionDialog.section-description: This section will appear at the end of your career page. It usually contains pages that link to your website, or contact information that direct candidates to your social media pages such as Facebook,Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn and YouTube. Customize and add the title, link type, and link for each page or category.
FooterSectionDialog.title: Title
